<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1892-02-13T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1892-02-13T00:00:00-05:00" n="550" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d550">
                        <head><hi rend="italic">Sir <persName type="from">Julian
                                    Pauncefote</persName> to Mr. <persName type="to">Blaine</persName></hi>.</head>
                        <opener><dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">British
                                        Legation</hi>,<lb/><hi rend="italic">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1892-02-13"><hi rend="italic">February 13,
                                    1892</hi></date>.</dateline></opener>
                        <p><hi rend="smallcaps">Sir</hi>: With reference to your note of the 4th
                            instant, inclosing a copy of the draft of the proposed Behring Sea
                            arbitration convention I have <pb facs="0721" n="613" xml:id="pg_613"/>
                            the honor to inform you that, as previously arranged between us, I
                            transmitted a copy of the draft by the mail of the 6th instant to the
                            Marquis of Salisbury for the approval of Her Majesty’s Government, and
                            that I am awaiting his lordship’s instructions before proceeding further
                            in the matter.</p>
                        <p>I have, etc.,</p>
                        <closer><signed><hi rend="smallcaps">Julian
                            Pauncefote</hi>.</signed></closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>